    <p><a href="http://jkaltes.byethost16.com/Juggluco/mmol.html">Juggluco</a>
      is now ported to Wear OS. It consists of an adaptation of the smartphone
      version to the smaller screen of the watch and a watch face that shows the
      time, the current glucose value received every minute and four
      complication slots.</p>
    <figure> <img src="menu1.png" style="object-fit:contain;height:4.5cm; width:auto;">
      <figcaption><span style="font-size: 0.9em; font-family: Times New Roman;">Left
          menu of Juggluco Wear</span></figcaption> </figure>
    <figure> <img src="menu2.png" style="object-fit:contain;height:4.5cm; width:auto;">
      <figcaption><span style="font-size: 0.9em; font-family: Times New Roman;">Right
          menu of Juggluco Wear</span></figcaption> </figure>
    <figure> <img src="watchface3.png" style="object-fit:contain;height:4.5cm; width:auto;">
      <figcaption><span style="font-size: 0.9em; font-family: Times New Roman;">Watch
          face with one complication and music playing</span></figcaption> </figure>
    <figure> <img src="value.png" style="object-fit:contain;height:4.5cm; width:auto;">
      <figcaption><span style="font-size: 0.9em; font-family: Times New Roman;">Juggluco
          Wear</span></figcaption> </figure>
    <p>Every sensor has to be initialized by the smartphone version of Juggluco,
      that sends the sensor data to the watch version. Thereafter, there are two
      possibilities:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>Keep the sensor connected with the smartphone and sends the data from
          the smartphone to the watch by TCP;</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>If you have a watch with good functioning Bluetooth, you can also try
          a direct connection between watch and sensor.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <figure> <img src="juggluco.png" style="object-fit:contain;height:4.5cm; width:auto;">
      <figcaption><span style="font-size: 0.9em; font-family: Times New Roman;">Juggluco
          Wear with amounts displayed</span></figcaption> </figure>
